ActFirst Nations Commercial and Industrial Development Act
Dominion Water Power Act
SubjectBlack Lake First Nation Water Power Regulations
PrecisBLACK LAKE FIRST NATION WATER POWER REGULATIONS in order to (1) remove regulatory barriers to economic development on-reserve to improve economic and social conditions for First Nation members; (2) increase opportunities for partnership-based economic development projects; (3) create positive and collaborative intergovernmental regulatory partnerships; (4) ensure that environmental, health and safety, and other related impacts common to hydroelectric production projects are effectively managed; and, (5) ensure co-operation between the federal and provincial governments on issues related to the ownership of water and water rights associated with this project.
